1
00:00:06,106 --> 00:00:08,640
Oh, yes! I know, I know...

2
00:00:08,641 --> 00:00:11,977
I'm so sorry. You didn't like that, huh?

3
00:00:11,978 --> 00:00:13,213
I am so sorry.

4
00:00:14,914 --> 00:00:18,051
Here we go. Let me hold you.

5
00:00:21,888 --> 00:00:23,523
Look at me. Over here.

6
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:30,195
I'm so sorry, Mari. So sorry.

7
00:00:30,196 --> 00:00:32,664
Auntie, it seems
that I'm not good enough for her.

8
00:00:32,665 --> 00:00:35,835
I'm so sorry. Are you crying?

9
00:00:36,669 --> 00:00:37,871
Is she your granddaughter?

10
00:00:38,838 --> 00:00:41,775
No, it's Mee's baby.
You know the part-timer we have?

11
00:00:43,309 --> 00:00:45,711
I'm so sorry. Thank you.

12
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:49,148
She's hospitalized
after breaking her leg in an accident.

13
00:00:49,149 --> 00:00:50,216
Are you serious?

14
00:00:52,085 --> 00:00:53,819
I didn't mind taking care of her,

15
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:57,190
but she's very active just like her mom.

16
00:00:58,291 --> 00:01:01,560
So, both Mee and you
are in tough situations.

17
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:02,961
Yeah, kind of.

18
00:01:02,962 --> 00:01:06,999
But we should help each other
in times of need.

19
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,568
Good girl. Do you want to eat?

20
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:12,038
Look. It's time to eat.

21
00:01:13,306 --> 00:01:17,476
- What's that?
- It's called <i>rousong,</i> or meat floss.

22
00:01:17,477 --> 00:01:18,410
<i>Rousong?</i>

23
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:20,279
This is Chinese food.

24
00:01:20,280 --> 00:01:24,583
It's dried pork and beef that's shredded
into a fluffy, powdery texture.

25
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:26,151
I want to try a little bit.

26
00:01:26,152 --> 00:01:27,686
- Do you want to?
- Sure.

27
00:01:27,687 --> 00:01:29,054
Just a little then.

28
00:01:29,055 --> 00:01:30,657
- There.
- Let's eat.

29
00:01:31,224 --> 00:01:33,293
And there...

30
00:01:35,361 --> 00:01:37,063
It's sweet and salty at the same time.

31
00:01:38,198 --> 00:01:41,667
Here you go.

32
00:01:41,668 --> 00:01:43,269
You're eating it.

33
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:44,870
Is that good?

34
00:01:44,871 --> 00:01:46,506
You're happy now.

35
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:49,608
- How adorable! She's smiling now.
- She loves this.

36
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:51,677
I'm so sorry, Mari.

37
00:01:51,678 --> 00:01:53,913
We are having such a hectic morning.

38
00:01:55,515 --> 00:01:57,617
Are you doing okay with your time?

39
00:01:59,119 --> 00:01:59,953
Oops.

40
00:02:01,888 --> 00:02:03,123
See you later.

41
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:05,524
- See you.
- Bye Mari.

42
00:02:05,525 --> 00:02:07,659
- Have a good day.
- Bye.

43
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:08,962
Be careful of cars.

44
00:02:18,905 --> 00:02:20,473
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

45
00:02:24,577 --> 00:02:25,744
Good morning.

46
00:02:25,745 --> 00:02:27,113
Koda!

47
00:02:28,081 --> 00:02:30,282
- Come over here.
- Yes?

48
00:02:30,283 --> 00:02:31,617
‎INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION DIVISION

49
00:02:31,618 --> 00:02:33,585
What time do you think it is?

50
00:02:33,586 --> 00:02:35,821
You think you're an executive or what?

51
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:36,890
No...

52
00:02:37,390 --> 00:02:41,059
I had some emergencies,
but I learned something this morning.

53
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:42,694
Do you know what <i>rousong</i> is?

54
00:02:42,695 --> 00:02:44,164
Stop right there.

55
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:46,666
You really haven't learned anything
from that incident, have you?

56
00:02:49,435 --> 00:02:50,470
You might fall someday

57
00:02:51,971 --> 00:02:55,408
if you follow only your convictions
in this organization.

58
00:02:56,543 --> 00:02:57,810
You'll reach a point of no return.

59
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:00,679
Listen.

60
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,616
Don't go around on your own.

61
00:03:04,284 --> 00:03:06,686
My former partner used to do that,
and I lost him.

62
00:03:07,287 --> 00:03:08,922
Learn before it's too late.

63
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:11,291
Arikeeno was the one
who leaked information?

64
00:03:11,891 --> 00:03:13,125
Not only that,

65
00:03:13,126 --> 00:03:16,029
but the article led to someone's death.

66
00:03:17,096 --> 00:03:18,397
Hey! Are you listening?

67
00:03:18,398 --> 00:03:20,232
Yes, I am. I am remorseful.

68
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:22,768
You're super professional at pretending.

69
00:03:22,769 --> 00:03:23,869
Thank you so much.

70
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,504
That wasn't a compliment.

71
00:03:25,505 --> 00:03:27,573
Easy, easy, easy...

72
00:03:27,574 --> 00:03:28,575
Okay?

73
00:03:32,078 --> 00:03:32,912
Hold on.

74
00:03:33,513 --> 00:03:36,248
Do something about your hair.
What's that color?

75
00:03:36,249 --> 00:03:37,416
It's neon green.

76
00:03:37,417 --> 00:03:39,285
- Ne... neon green?
- Neon green.

77
00:03:40,019 --> 00:03:42,521
An investigator shouldn't draw
too much attention.

78
00:03:42,522 --> 00:03:44,490
It's supposed to be dark like black.

79
00:03:45,358 --> 00:03:47,192
Follow my great example.

80
00:03:47,193 --> 00:03:49,728
I'm not so sure
about following your example.

81
00:03:49,729 --> 00:03:51,998
Maybe you can follow his... You know...

82
00:03:53,466 --> 00:03:56,069
Don't look at me like that. I was just...

83
00:03:58,871 --> 00:04:01,840
That must have been hell for you.

84
00:04:01,841 --> 00:04:04,811
I got burned pretty badly.

85
00:04:05,812 --> 00:04:10,016
But I admit, he does have a point.

86
00:04:10,516 --> 00:04:13,920
I'm afraid his blood pressure
will rise above 200 because of me.

87
00:04:14,621 --> 00:04:16,922
Then, at least undo your hair color.

88
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:20,392
But there are no regulations
on police officers' hairstyles.

89
00:04:20,393 --> 00:04:23,061
Still, you should look
more like a police officer.

90
00:04:23,062 --> 00:04:25,164
For goodness' sake, learn from Kana.

91
00:04:25,665 --> 00:04:26,698
But I'm not... Um...

92
00:04:26,699 --> 00:04:28,334
How about those guys' styles?

93
00:04:28,835 --> 00:04:31,203
Mr. Tarao must have had yakuza-style hair

94
00:04:31,204 --> 00:04:33,105
when he was with
the Organized Crime Division.

95
00:04:33,106 --> 00:04:35,707
They look like that
because they have to, in a way.

96
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:39,012
I have this hairstyle out of necessity.
It's my signature.

97
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:42,148
You're such a contrarian.

98
00:04:48,821 --> 00:04:49,955
Thank you for your help.

99
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:51,324
Thank you very much.

100
00:04:53,192 --> 00:04:56,129
Tomica, as I know,
it is impossible to find this...

101
00:05:05,938 --> 00:05:08,707
Hikari-oka? You mean,
Hikarigaoka in Nerima Ward?

102
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:09,976
I got it.

103
00:05:18,084 --> 00:05:21,153
<i>Banh mi</i> and Vietnamese coffee?
Coffee with condensed milk, right?

104
00:05:21,154 --> 00:05:21,820
Yes.

105
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:23,055
The coffee must be really sweet.

106
00:05:23,056 --> 00:05:24,489
I'd love to try it.

107
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:26,258
- Sounds good.
- It's delicious.

108
00:05:26,259 --> 00:05:27,527
All right.

109
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:31,631
Oh, Arikeeno. Arikeeno. Wait.

110
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:38,304
I didn't realize you were here.

111
00:05:38,805 --> 00:05:39,638
I'm here.

112
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:41,506
‎INTERROGATION ROOM

113
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:42,442
Um...

114
00:05:45,211 --> 00:05:47,647
About the other day... I'm sorry.

115
00:05:50,383 --> 00:05:52,084
You know, Shen was saying

116
00:05:52,085 --> 00:05:55,922
she wants to go out to eat together again.
Would you like to join us?

117
00:05:56,489 --> 00:05:58,658
Don't talk about that now. I'm on duty.

118
00:06:00,393 --> 00:06:04,596
I'm interviewing a witness
in a drugstore shoplifting case.

119
00:06:04,597 --> 00:06:06,331
Our interpreter isn't here yet,

120
00:06:06,332 --> 00:06:10,302
so I was asking which restaurant
serves authentic Vietnamese food.

121
00:06:10,303 --> 00:06:11,270
When will you be free?

122
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:13,906
I'm working...

123
00:06:16,609 --> 00:06:17,477
until Friday.

124
00:06:19,445 --> 00:06:22,047
I see. All right then--

125
00:06:22,048 --> 00:06:23,649
I'm sorry I'm late.

126
00:06:25,618 --> 00:06:27,586
You had something to discuss
with Miss Koda?

127
00:06:27,587 --> 00:06:28,654
Not really.

128
00:06:29,922 --> 00:06:31,924
There's quite a commotion
going on in here.

129
00:06:34,093 --> 00:06:35,795
The Detective Division is here.

130
00:06:36,362 --> 00:06:37,663
I wonder if something happened.

131
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:44,870
- Excuse me. I'll go leave my stuff.
- Take your time.

132
00:06:44,871 --> 00:06:45,937
Hello?

133
00:06:45,938 --> 00:06:50,042
<i>Mr. Arikino, there's a Code 224 incident
at Higashi Shinjuku Police Station.</i>

134
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:52,712
What? A Code 224 incident?

135
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,681
Kidnapping?

136
00:07:08,494 --> 00:07:09,762
- Let's hurry up.
- Yes, sir.

137
00:07:22,175 --> 00:07:23,041
INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION DIVISION

138
00:07:23,042 --> 00:07:25,844
- The victim is a 1-year-old boy.
- Yes.

139
00:07:25,845 --> 00:07:28,447
His mother is a naturalized citizen
from China,

140
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,916
so we urgently requested an interpreter.

141
00:07:30,917 --> 00:07:31,983
I see.

142
00:07:31,984 --> 00:07:34,519
I specifically asked for Mr. Arikino,

143
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,721
who was a great help
with the Koda incident.

144
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:40,058
And the First Division will take charge
of the incident room.

145
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:41,326
Okay.

146
00:07:41,327 --> 00:07:45,363
Our Detective Division is allocating
manpower, but they want one person

147
00:07:45,364 --> 00:07:46,765
from the International Division.

148
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:48,166
From our division?

149
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:50,602
Since it's a clandestine operation,

150
00:07:50,603 --> 00:07:53,239
an investigator who doesn't look
like a detective would be ideal.

151
00:08:02,615 --> 00:08:05,550
I'm so sorry. Sorry. Oh my God!

152
00:08:05,551 --> 00:08:06,451
Oh my God!

153
00:08:06,452 --> 00:08:10,189
Hello, Happy Green!
Are you doing well today?

154
00:08:12,191 --> 00:08:14,559
- Hey. You're splashing all over.
- I'm so sorry.

155
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:17,329
Why don't you spray it directly
on the plant?

156
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:19,898
- Okay.
- Hey, come on. Stop.

157
00:08:19,899 --> 00:08:21,033
Shakuno, can I have a word?

158
00:08:22,134 --> 00:08:23,102
What did you say?

159
00:08:23,803 --> 00:08:25,137
You want me to go to the incident room?

160
00:08:27,573 --> 00:08:30,877
Do your best as the representative
of our division.

161
00:08:31,677 --> 00:08:34,580
This is a once-in-a-lifetime chance
for you.

162
00:08:36,249 --> 00:08:40,286
Don't vacillate, Shakuno. You've got this.

163
00:08:43,055 --> 00:08:43,890
Yes, sir.

164
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:47,559
At around 11:20 am today,

165
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:51,898
a one-year-old boy went missing
from his residence in Higashiochiai.

166
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:08,146
Junjun, Mommy is going to do
some cleaning, all right?

167
00:09:08,147 --> 00:09:10,782
<i>The mother says she went shopping
with the boy</i>

168
00:09:10,783 --> 00:09:14,786
<i>and came home with him
sometime after eleven o’clock today.</i>

169
00:09:14,787 --> 00:09:17,123
<i>She let him play by himself
in the living room</i>

170
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:19,324
<i>while she did some chores.</i>

171
00:09:19,325 --> 00:09:22,694
<i>It seems that the incident occurred
in the brief moment</i>

172
00:09:22,695 --> 00:09:24,897
<i>when she was cleaning the bathroom.</i>

173
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:49,422
Junjun.

174
00:09:52,124 --> 00:09:52,959
Junjun?

175
00:09:57,363 --> 00:09:58,230
Junjun?

176
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:01,000
Junjun?

177
00:10:03,069 --> 00:10:03,903
Junjun?

178
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,975
Junjun?

179
00:10:12,211 --> 00:10:17,984
Junjun?

180
00:10:19,685 --> 00:10:21,987
The kidnapped boy's name
is Shun Harashima.

181
00:10:21,988 --> 00:10:22,887
SHUN HARASHIMA

182
00:10:22,888 --> 00:10:24,089
He lives with his Japanese father

183
00:10:24,090 --> 00:10:26,791
and his Chinese mother,
who is a naturalized citizen.

184
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:27,692
YUKI HARASHIMA, KOJI HARASHIMA

185
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:30,061
He can stand up
while holding onto something,

186
00:10:30,062 --> 00:10:31,763
but he can barely walk yet.

187
00:10:31,764 --> 00:10:35,367
It should be noted that the living room
patio door was left open,

188
00:10:35,368 --> 00:10:39,537
and there were footprints,
likely belonging to the intruder.

189
00:10:39,538 --> 00:10:43,241
Based on these facts, we presume
the boy was taken by the intruder

190
00:10:43,242 --> 00:10:47,179
and are investigating this incident
as a minor's kidnapping.

191
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:49,081
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

192
00:10:51,384 --> 00:10:52,984
- I'm off to the crime scene.
- Got it.

193
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,953
YUKI HARASHIMA 35 YEARS OLD

194
00:10:54,954 --> 00:10:56,789
KOJI HARASHIMA 39 YEARS OLD

195
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:01,560
Sawada Appliances.
Here to install your washing machine.

196
00:11:09,969 --> 00:11:11,103
Come on in.

197
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:12,971
One, two, three.

198
00:11:12,972 --> 00:11:14,140
‎SAWADA APPLIANCES

199
00:11:17,176 --> 00:11:18,043
There.

200
00:11:18,044 --> 00:11:21,981
HARASHIMA KOJI, YUKI, SHUN

201
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:24,783
I'm Yasunaga

202
00:11:24,784 --> 00:11:27,319
from the Tokyo Metropolitan PD's
Special Investigation Unit.

203
00:11:27,887 --> 00:11:30,022
Shakuno, Fujimoto,
and I will be handling this case.

204
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:34,760
I'm Koji Harashima.

205
00:11:35,895 --> 00:11:37,963
This is our interpreter,
who speaks Chinese.

206
00:11:38,564 --> 00:11:40,466
We'll speak with your wife as well.

207
00:11:42,234 --> 00:11:43,369
Where's your wife?

208
00:11:45,805 --> 00:11:47,039
She's resting upstairs.

209
00:11:49,508 --> 00:11:51,010
- Can you come with me?
- Yes, ma'am.

210
00:11:54,180 --> 00:11:57,315
To avoid alerting the kidnapper
to our involvement,

211
00:11:57,316 --> 00:12:00,052
try to live your life
as normally as possible.

212
00:12:02,621 --> 00:12:03,756
If you don't mind,

213
00:12:04,256 --> 00:12:07,159
how about I start the conversation
with her in Chinese?

214
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:08,561
Huh?

215
00:12:09,762 --> 00:12:11,763
It might be easier for her
psychologically.

216
00:12:11,764 --> 00:12:13,332
I'll update you on what I said.

217
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:17,503
All right. Go ahead.

218
00:12:23,609 --> 00:12:24,810
Excuse me.

219
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:34,620
I'm Arikino, an interpreter.

220
00:12:35,387 --> 00:12:37,389
Do you mind if we ask you a few questions?

221
00:12:41,660 --> 00:12:43,496
It's not like I make a lot of money,

222
00:12:44,096 --> 00:12:45,598
and I got a loan for this house.

223
00:12:47,099 --> 00:12:49,467
If they're after ransom,

224
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:52,171
there are plenty of other houses
with wealthier people, don't you think?

225
00:12:54,907 --> 00:12:56,375
Why would they take our child?

226
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:01,747
The motive for kidnappings
isn't always money.

227
00:13:02,648 --> 00:13:07,520
Can you think of anyone
you've had trouble with in the past?

228
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:13,658
Are you saying Shun was kidnapped
because of me?

229
00:13:13,659 --> 00:13:15,427
That's not what I meant.

230
00:13:16,061 --> 00:13:18,229
If the motive isn't ransom,

231
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:21,167
another motive we can
think of is a grudge.

232
00:13:22,601 --> 00:13:24,636
To create a profile of the unsub,

233
00:13:24,637 --> 00:13:27,373
we need to understand your
and your wife's history.

234
00:13:31,110 --> 00:13:33,412
When did you come to Japan?

235
00:13:34,446 --> 00:13:35,714
Six years ago.

236
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:38,350
I was 29 years old then.

237
00:13:41,086 --> 00:13:42,288
When did you get married?

238
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:45,758
Four years ago.

239
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,596
Koji and I met at my workplace.

240
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:53,732
Then, Shun was born.

241
00:13:55,701 --> 00:13:56,968
Why would he?

242
00:13:56,969 --> 00:13:59,839
Why would my son be kidnapped
in this country?

243
00:14:01,874 --> 00:14:06,712
I thought I would be safe if I married
a Japanese man and became Japanese.

244
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:08,948
Why?

245
00:14:10,082 --> 00:14:13,786
Why on earth was my son taken?

246
00:14:21,794 --> 00:14:24,763
Could you please keep an eye on my wife?

247
00:14:26,232 --> 00:14:27,233
We will.

248
00:14:42,781 --> 00:14:43,915
Mrs. Harashima used to work

249
00:14:43,916 --> 00:14:47,119
at a nightclub called Marmol,
located in Takadanobaba.

250
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:50,122
And Mr. Harashima
was one of her customers.

251
00:14:50,856 --> 00:14:52,791
Does she have a part-time job now?

252
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:56,228
Since having a baby,
she's been a homemaker.

253
00:14:57,930 --> 00:14:59,964
She hasn't enrolled the child in daycare.

254
00:14:59,965 --> 00:15:01,100
I see...

255
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:05,304
Thank you. I'll look into it.

256
00:15:08,474 --> 00:15:11,343
Your division seems to have a lot
going on with this case.

257
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:16,649
But so far, I'm the only one
chosen to be a part of it.

258
00:15:20,019 --> 00:15:22,120
That's right. That's so green!

259
00:15:22,121 --> 00:15:23,755
TOKYO METROPOLITAN POLICE
INTERPRETATION CENTER

260
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:26,358
- Is that even possible?
- Anyone would think that.

261
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:28,961
It really freaked me out.

262
00:15:29,695 --> 00:15:31,095
On my way back
from the Higashi Shinjuku Police Station,

263
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,630
I went to buy a facial toner.

264
00:15:32,631 --> 00:15:33,998
Guess who was there?

265
00:15:33,999 --> 00:15:35,867
Miss Koda was working in the store.

266
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:38,370
She's like, "Welcome to our store!"

267
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:42,006
- You mean at that drugstore over there?
- Yes.

268
00:15:42,007 --> 00:15:44,008
It seems she's undercover for some reason.

269
00:15:44,009 --> 00:15:45,777
- Undercover?
- Yep.

270
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:48,212
I can totally imagine
Miss Koda blending in.

271
00:15:48,213 --> 00:15:50,048
Yeah. Like a professional.

272
00:15:50,049 --> 00:15:53,151
She was serving customers
like she'd been working there forever.

273
00:15:53,152 --> 00:15:54,185
That's incredible.

274
00:15:54,186 --> 00:15:57,088
Speaking of skin toner,
you really take care of yourself, huh?

275
00:15:57,089 --> 00:15:59,724
DRUGSTORE

276
00:15:59,725 --> 00:16:00,759
Welcome to our store.

277
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:03,762
Three of these for you, right?

278
00:16:05,831 --> 00:16:08,533
Excuse me, where can I find
the fabric softeners?

279
00:16:08,534 --> 00:16:12,070
Fabric softeners?
They're in aisle 14 at the back.

280
00:16:12,071 --> 00:16:13,137
Excuse me.

281
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:15,773
Manager, could you assist this lady
over here?

282
00:16:15,774 --> 00:16:18,843
- All right. Let me show you.
- Thank you for your patience.

283
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:21,679
We're offering free samples
of this product as part of a campaign.

284
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:23,314
Feel free to try it.

285
00:16:23,315 --> 00:16:24,616
Thank you so much.

286
00:16:25,117 --> 00:16:27,452
- And here's your receipt.
- Thanks.

287
00:16:27,453 --> 00:16:29,621
Thank you so much.

288
00:16:30,622 --> 00:16:33,492
Next, please. Welcome to our store.

289
00:16:34,393 --> 00:16:35,227
Arikeeno?

290
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:38,764
What are you doing here?

291
00:16:40,366 --> 00:16:41,400
Well...

292
00:16:42,401 --> 00:16:43,836
I could ask you the same thing.

293
00:16:46,305 --> 00:16:47,573
Welcome to our store!

294
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:52,745
Do you remember the witness
from the drugstore shoplifting case?

295
00:16:57,916 --> 00:17:02,487
It seemed
that man was part of a shoplifting ring.

296
00:17:02,488 --> 00:17:04,423
That's why I'm at this <i>dorasto</i>.

297
00:17:05,224 --> 00:17:07,426
- <i>Dorasto?</i>
- It means "drugstore."

298
00:17:08,761 --> 00:17:12,196
You didn't know?
You're so behind the times.

299
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:15,500
But that's what's great about you.

300
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:17,436
- And?
- And...

301
00:17:18,070 --> 00:17:21,005
there have been
many shoplifting incidents here.

302
00:17:21,006 --> 00:17:23,041
Besides, the only thing they ever steal

303
00:17:23,809 --> 00:17:25,444
is diapers.

304
00:17:26,412 --> 00:17:27,245
Diapers?

305
00:17:27,246 --> 00:17:28,946
Did you know that Japanese diapers

306
00:17:28,947 --> 00:17:33,685
are renowned for their quality
and are highly sought after overseas?

307
00:17:34,319 --> 00:17:35,219
Really?

308
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:37,388
So, I proposed to our division manager

309
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:40,725
that we plant a GPS device
in disposable diapers at this store.

310
00:17:40,726 --> 00:17:44,163
Because that will help us
get to the bottom of it.

311
00:17:44,997 --> 00:17:47,598
But he said that before I begin
an undercover investigation,

312
00:17:47,599 --> 00:17:50,436
I need to confirm the existence
of a shoplifting ring.

313
00:17:51,770 --> 00:17:52,971
But why work in the store?

314
00:17:53,605 --> 00:17:57,076
It's too boring to just keep watching
the monitors, don't you think?

315
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:00,879
Besides, they told me
that they were understaffed.

316
00:18:02,848 --> 00:18:04,917
You're going off on your own again.

317
00:18:05,417 --> 00:18:07,219
What will you do if you end up
in danger again?

318
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:10,988
Do you feel sorry
for what happened last time?

319
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:12,791
Of course, I do.

320
00:18:13,525 --> 00:18:16,795
And this time,
I'm really thinking things through.

321
00:18:17,830 --> 00:18:18,864
Right, Kana?

322
00:18:19,898 --> 00:18:21,066
Welcome to our store.

323
00:18:22,468 --> 00:18:25,337
Happy shopping!

324
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:32,410
Thanks so much for coming
to see me. I'm glad we could talk.

325
00:18:32,411 --> 00:18:35,481
No. I didn't come here to see you.

326
00:18:36,748 --> 00:18:37,716
Goodbye, then.

327
00:18:40,352 --> 00:18:42,154
Come shop with us again.

328
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:51,263
Let's eat.

329
00:18:56,201 --> 00:18:57,135
It's delicious.

330
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:58,737
Yes, it's delicious.

331
00:19:03,509 --> 00:19:04,476
Mari?

332
00:19:06,078 --> 00:19:09,114
I think I'm interested after all.

333
00:19:09,615 --> 00:19:12,850
What? You mean,
you're interested in Arikeeno?

334
00:19:12,851 --> 00:19:15,254
No. It's not that.

335
00:19:16,288 --> 00:19:18,222
Do you remember when we talked

336
00:19:18,223 --> 00:19:20,659
about interpreting with Mr. Arikino
the other day?

337
00:19:21,693 --> 00:19:23,061
I found it very interesting.

338
00:19:23,962 --> 00:19:27,766
I like the work of interpreters.

339
00:19:29,101 --> 00:19:31,904
Oh, that's what you meant.

340
00:19:33,038 --> 00:19:35,040
That's great.

341
00:19:36,275 --> 00:19:37,542
<i>"Nyu"?</i>

342
00:19:37,543 --> 00:19:39,377
<i>"Niu"?</i> Awesome?

343
00:19:39,378 --> 00:19:41,113
<i>"Niu,"</i> I guess.

344
00:19:43,248 --> 00:19:44,582
I want to become an interpreter.

345
00:19:44,583 --> 00:19:46,451
That's my new dream for the future.

346
00:19:47,319 --> 00:19:48,786
You inspired me.

347
00:19:48,787 --> 00:19:51,689
No way. It was Arikeeno
who inspired you, wasn't it?

348
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:54,226
No. It was you, Mari.

349
00:19:54,927 --> 00:19:58,564
You understand people's hearts very well.

350
00:19:59,264 --> 00:20:03,167
That's a very important quality
for interpreters.

351
00:20:03,168 --> 00:20:05,637
That's what Mr. Arikino told me.

352
00:20:09,975 --> 00:20:13,312
Both of you understand people's hearts.

353
00:20:15,514 --> 00:20:18,951
You are great with each other.

354
00:20:25,090 --> 00:20:28,994
I'm going to be busy with my classes
from now on.

355
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:34,600
I want to ask you to understand
Mr. Arikino's feelings.

356
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:37,636
I like both of you very much.

357
00:20:44,142 --> 00:20:45,244
Thank you.

358
00:20:47,045 --> 00:20:49,848
I like you very much, too.

359
00:20:54,519 --> 00:20:55,988
Sweet Mari.

360
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:03,729
DAY TWO SINCE THE KIDNAPPING

361
00:21:07,499 --> 00:21:10,001
<i>There hasn't been any contact
from the kidnapper</i>

362
00:21:10,002 --> 00:21:13,138
<i>about a ransom or any other demands.</i>

363
00:21:13,972 --> 00:21:15,339
<i>Considering the child's wellbeing,</i>

364
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:18,777
<i>we must avoid delaying the resolution
of this case.</i>

365
00:21:20,078 --> 00:21:22,581
Share with the group
if you have any new information.

366
00:21:25,083 --> 00:21:26,018
Kuroiwa.

367
00:21:31,857 --> 00:21:35,826
The forensic report on the footprints
left in the living room

368
00:21:35,827 --> 00:21:39,931
indicates they were made by sneakers
from a major American manufacturer.

369
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:43,367
But because there are
so many of them out there,

370
00:21:43,368 --> 00:21:47,372
it could take a very long time
to narrow down the purchasers.

371
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:49,374
That's all.

372
00:21:53,612 --> 00:21:54,513
Any other information?

373
00:21:58,216 --> 00:21:59,217
Mr. Yanagi?

374
00:22:01,653 --> 00:22:03,088
Go ahead, Yanagi.

375
00:22:04,523 --> 00:22:07,758
Neither the father, Koji Harashima,
nor the mother, Yuki Harashima,

376
00:22:07,759 --> 00:22:10,629
seem to have any history of trouble.

377
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:15,367
They have a good relationship
and are liked by their neighbors.

378
00:22:19,771 --> 00:22:20,972
Arikino.

379
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:27,546
It's been a while.

380
00:22:28,947 --> 00:22:30,582
Why on earth are you here?

381
00:22:34,152 --> 00:22:36,555
I'm asking you why on earth you are here.

382
00:22:40,826 --> 00:22:42,594
You shouldn't be here at all.

383
00:22:43,261 --> 00:22:46,565
How dare you have
the audacity to come here?

384
00:22:47,065 --> 00:22:48,867
You left the police force, didn't you?

385
00:22:50,402 --> 00:22:51,436
Hi, Arikeeno!

386
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:54,806
Oops. Am I interrupting you?

387
00:22:55,407 --> 00:22:56,608
You are...

388
00:22:57,109 --> 00:22:59,344
Good afternoon, Mr. Shiny Red Button.

389
00:23:01,179 --> 00:23:02,714
Is the briefing finished now?

390
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:05,851
Yes...

391
00:23:06,351 --> 00:23:08,886
If so, I'm sorry I'm taking this guy
with me.

392
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:10,021
Excuse us.

393
00:23:10,756 --> 00:23:14,158
Let's go have lunch.
I brought us some food.

394
00:23:14,159 --> 00:23:15,160
Come on, let's go.

395
00:23:20,565 --> 00:23:22,032
Drawing unnecessary attention

396
00:23:22,033 --> 00:23:24,536
from the First Division
could cause future trouble.

397
00:23:25,604 --> 00:23:27,973
He sure does look like trouble.

398
00:23:30,542 --> 00:23:34,545
That was Lieutenant Yanagi,
one of the elites in the First Division.

399
00:23:34,546 --> 00:23:35,580
Is that right?

400
00:23:36,181 --> 00:23:38,417
And what was he so upset about?

401
00:23:40,685 --> 00:23:41,553
Well...

402
00:23:43,688 --> 00:23:47,626
It's because I caused him
a lot of trouble in the past.

403
00:23:49,261 --> 00:23:51,530
I see...

404
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:55,233
Come on, let's eat now.

405
00:23:57,335 --> 00:23:58,903
<i>Banh mi!</i>

406
00:23:58,904 --> 00:24:00,172
Here you go.

407
00:24:02,107 --> 00:24:03,407
What's this?

408
00:24:03,408 --> 00:24:04,543
It's <i>banh mi</i>.

409
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:07,546
It's from the shop I told you about.

410
00:24:08,213 --> 00:24:10,549
I was really craving it.

411
00:24:11,316 --> 00:24:13,752
And here's some Vietnamese coffee.

412
00:24:14,619 --> 00:24:15,520
For you.

413
00:24:16,254 --> 00:24:18,690
Come on, let's eat.

414
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:21,126
There.

415
00:24:31,269 --> 00:24:33,004
It looks so good.

416
00:24:43,682 --> 00:24:44,683
It's very good.

417
00:24:46,685 --> 00:24:48,720
It's somewhat like a baguette,

418
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:53,058
but how can I say it?
It's crispier and chewier.

419
00:24:55,327 --> 00:24:59,129
There's chicken liver pâté,

420
00:24:59,130 --> 00:25:02,700
along with tangy pickled
daikon radish and carrot.

421
00:25:02,701 --> 00:25:04,236
This is a great combination.

422
00:25:04,736 --> 00:25:08,672
At first, I thought it was strange
to put them in bread.

423
00:25:08,673 --> 00:25:10,075
But it's a great invention.

424
00:25:10,809 --> 00:25:12,810
I wonder if it's a sign

425
00:25:12,811 --> 00:25:15,580
that Vietnamese people are geniuses
at adapting things.

426
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:19,751
Are you talking to me?

427
00:25:20,785 --> 00:25:22,420
Who else do I have here?

428
00:25:30,428 --> 00:25:34,499
When you think about it,
people and food culture

429
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:39,604
have crossed country borders
and transcended boundaries.

430
00:25:41,273 --> 00:25:44,910
And they continue to evolve
after reaching their destinations.

431
00:25:46,845 --> 00:25:48,713
Don't you think it's amazing?

432
00:25:49,981 --> 00:25:51,249
It's such a blessing.

433
00:25:59,724 --> 00:26:00,926
I'm eating, too, then.

434
00:26:29,220 --> 00:26:31,522
DAY THREE SINCE THE KIDNAPPING

435
00:26:31,523 --> 00:26:33,925
The kidnapper hasn't made any contact yet.

436
00:26:35,193 --> 00:26:37,428
What about the security camera footage?

437
00:26:37,429 --> 00:26:38,529
Here's the thing.

438
00:26:38,530 --> 00:26:40,297
We've been carefully reviewing footage

439
00:26:40,298 --> 00:26:42,634
from all the cameras around their place.

440
00:26:43,268 --> 00:26:45,736
But I haven't confirmed
the exact time he was taken,

441
00:26:45,737 --> 00:26:49,441
and I haven't seen anyone suspicious
or even Shun himself.

442
00:26:52,277 --> 00:26:53,411
Excuse me.

443
00:26:53,979 --> 00:26:58,416
Sir, some information about the father
has caught my attention.

444
00:27:06,224 --> 00:27:07,726
- Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

445
00:27:22,841 --> 00:27:23,874
Good afternoon.

446
00:27:23,875 --> 00:27:27,646
I'm Yanagi from the First Division.
Could we have a word?

447
00:27:28,913 --> 00:27:29,980
Sure.

448
00:27:29,981 --> 00:27:33,117
You've borrowed
around 2.5 million yen in total

449
00:27:33,118 --> 00:27:35,553
from consumer finance companies,
haven't you?

450
00:27:37,922 --> 00:27:42,427
And one million yen of that
is borrowed from a high-interest company.

451
00:27:42,994 --> 00:27:43,694
PROOF OF PAYMENT

452
00:27:43,695 --> 00:27:47,098
But you paid back all of it
all at once last month.

453
00:27:47,699 --> 00:27:51,469
Can you tell us where
all that money came from?

454
00:27:53,772 --> 00:27:56,074
Why do you need to dig up
such information?

455
00:27:57,042 --> 00:27:58,243
I'm sorry.

456
00:27:58,743 --> 00:28:01,012
We're just trying to find
any possible clues.

457
00:28:02,313 --> 00:28:04,182
Will you please answer my question?

458
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:08,353
Why don't you hurry up and find my son?

459
00:28:09,320 --> 00:28:11,322
It's been three days
since he went missing.

460
00:28:12,457 --> 00:28:14,892
What the heck are the police even doing?

461
00:28:14,893 --> 00:28:16,928
Why haven't you been able to find my son?

462
00:28:17,796 --> 00:28:20,664
We want to rescue your son
as much as you do.

463
00:28:20,665 --> 00:28:24,235
Not as much as we do. Shun is my son.

464
00:28:25,737 --> 00:28:26,571
Listen now.

465
00:28:27,672 --> 00:28:29,908
Confirming that your debt isn't related

466
00:28:30,809 --> 00:28:33,478
allows us to rule out one possible motive.

467
00:28:36,581 --> 00:28:38,750
You repaid your debt of one million yen.

468
00:28:39,751 --> 00:28:40,919
So please tell us.

469
00:28:42,487 --> 00:28:43,922
Where did you get the money?

470
00:28:53,465 --> 00:28:56,634
Thank you so much. Shop with us again.

471
00:29:02,173 --> 00:29:03,775
Excuse me, Miss Koda.

472
00:29:04,375 --> 00:29:05,342
Yes?

473
00:29:05,343 --> 00:29:07,445
You're doing your work perfectly.

474
00:29:08,413 --> 00:29:10,180
Do you have prior experience?

475
00:29:10,181 --> 00:29:13,752
Actually, no. But I find
serving customers really enjoyable.

476
00:29:14,319 --> 00:29:16,587
You're well-suited for this job.

477
00:29:16,588 --> 00:29:17,756
Miss Koda,

478
00:29:18,690 --> 00:29:20,891
why not quit your police job
and work here?

479
00:29:20,892 --> 00:29:22,160
Manager!

480
00:29:23,328 --> 00:29:24,996
- I'm sorry.
- Thanks.

481
00:29:25,497 --> 00:29:28,333
Miss Koda, Miss Koda, Miss Koda...

482
00:29:28,967 --> 00:29:30,901
I saw someone suspicious
in the diaper aisle.

483
00:29:30,902 --> 00:29:32,035
What?

484
00:29:32,036 --> 00:29:34,471
He's been at the same spot
for over ten minutes now.

485
00:29:34,472 --> 00:29:37,175
Maybe he's part of a shoplifting ring.

486
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:39,943
Shall we go there?

487
00:29:39,944 --> 00:29:41,880
- Let's go.
- Wait...

488
00:29:43,014 --> 00:29:46,017
- Manager, I'm leaving the register to you.
- What?

489
00:29:51,022 --> 00:29:52,590
- Is that the man?
- Yes, that's him.

490
00:30:11,409 --> 00:30:13,044
Welcome to our store.

491
00:30:13,912 --> 00:30:15,280
Welcome to our store.

492
00:30:16,114 --> 00:30:17,247
How can I help you?

493
00:30:17,248 --> 00:30:20,952
‎SEICHO CHEMICALS

494
00:30:21,719 --> 00:30:24,055
Do you know which size you're looking for?

495
00:30:25,390 --> 00:30:27,091
Um...

496
00:30:28,159 --> 00:30:29,794
The baby's backside is...

497
00:30:31,062 --> 00:30:32,163
about this size.

498
00:30:34,332 --> 00:30:35,366
Very cute.

499
00:30:40,772 --> 00:30:42,339
- About this size?
- Yes.

500
00:30:42,340 --> 00:30:43,942
Very cute, right?

501
00:30:45,043 --> 00:30:46,344
Then...

502
00:30:47,979 --> 00:30:49,180
maybe this is the size.

503
00:30:51,149 --> 00:30:53,518
- I recommend this one to you.
- Okay.

504
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:55,587
Thank you.

505
00:30:56,955 --> 00:30:58,556
Thank you for shopping with us.

506
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:14,873
Hi there, Arikeeno.

507
00:31:18,743 --> 00:31:20,111
Hi to you too.

508
00:31:21,779 --> 00:31:22,747
And?

509
00:31:23,248 --> 00:31:25,583
Any progress with the kidnapping case?

510
00:31:28,686 --> 00:31:29,654
I can't tell you.

511
00:31:30,588 --> 00:31:32,156
That's strictly confidential.

512
00:31:33,591 --> 00:31:35,326
Strictly confidential?

513
00:31:38,963 --> 00:31:40,832
Do you think I'm stupid or what?

514
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:43,401
I'm sorry.

515
00:31:49,407 --> 00:31:50,375
You know,

516
00:31:51,542 --> 00:31:54,178
I was just thinking
about the boy's parents.

517
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:56,347
Probably,

518
00:31:57,015 --> 00:32:01,452
they never imagined facing an incident
like this in Japan today.

519
00:32:04,255 --> 00:32:06,024
- Don't you think?
- Thanks.

520
00:32:08,393 --> 00:32:10,528
The wife is deeply devastated.

521
00:32:11,195 --> 00:32:13,264
She's a naturalized citizen from China.

522
00:32:14,632 --> 00:32:15,600
I see.

523
00:32:23,374 --> 00:32:26,878
Kidnappings happen
in every country, but in China,

524
00:32:27,378 --> 00:32:31,716
they say that child abduction
and trafficking are ancient evils.

525
00:32:39,557 --> 00:32:40,991
What's this website?

526
00:32:40,992 --> 00:32:44,494
It's called <i>"Zhao ge ying er."</i>
It means, "find babies".

527
00:32:44,495 --> 00:32:47,999
It's a Chinese online bulletin board
for finding missing babies.

528
00:32:54,973 --> 00:32:56,040
There are so many...

529
00:33:06,584 --> 00:33:08,652
The majority of human
trafficking worldwide

530
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:11,489
is for sexual exploitation.

531
00:33:12,523 --> 00:33:15,026
However, China has a unique situation.

532
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:16,828
Unique situation?

533
00:33:18,062 --> 00:33:20,897
Boys are abducted and sold
to wealthy families without heirs

534
00:33:20,898 --> 00:33:23,034
or to farmers needing workers.

535
00:33:24,502 --> 00:33:28,206
On the other hand, among girls,
teens are more likely to be targeted.

536
00:33:28,873 --> 00:33:31,542
In many cases, they are kidnapped
and sold as brides.

537
00:33:33,945 --> 00:33:35,079
That's awful.

538
00:33:38,282 --> 00:33:42,819
Unaware of what might be happening
to their children,

539
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:44,355
the parents continue searching.

540
00:33:46,324 --> 00:33:48,526
Only a few are ever found.

541
00:33:50,161 --> 00:33:51,429
Arikeeno,

542
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,631
you sure know a lot, don't you?

543
00:33:55,633 --> 00:33:57,602
Did you learn about this as a cop?

544
00:33:59,771 --> 00:34:00,671
Um...

545
00:34:04,609 --> 00:34:05,543
Actually,

546
00:34:06,344 --> 00:34:09,580
I grew up in a city called Dalian
until I was 15.

547
00:34:10,181 --> 00:34:11,815
My parents used to say to me,

548
00:34:11,816 --> 00:34:14,786
"Always stay close
or you will be kidnapped."

549
00:34:15,686 --> 00:34:17,889
Is that right?

550
00:34:20,658 --> 00:34:21,859
It must have been hard for you.

551
00:34:23,194 --> 00:34:24,027
Huh?

552
00:34:24,028 --> 00:34:26,663
I mean, coming from Dalian around that age

553
00:34:26,664 --> 00:34:30,401
and attending a Japanese school
must have been tough.

554
00:34:31,102 --> 00:34:35,239
People might have a positive image
of growing up overseas.

555
00:34:36,340 --> 00:34:38,676
Some say, "It's nice
you speak two languages."

556
00:34:42,647 --> 00:34:46,384
Even if you grew up overseas,
it doesn't necessarily mean

557
00:34:46,884 --> 00:34:50,588
you can speak both languages
perfectly, does it?

558
00:34:53,291 --> 00:34:56,460
Besides, interpreting for the police
requires more

559
00:34:56,461 --> 00:35:00,131
than just understanding
and speaking the languages.

560
00:35:01,466 --> 00:35:04,001
So, I can imagine how hard
you must have worked

561
00:35:04,502 --> 00:35:08,039
to be able to do what you are doing now.

562
00:35:08,606 --> 00:35:10,675
You know what I mean?

563
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:20,718
RYUTA YANAGI

564
00:35:23,287 --> 00:35:24,122
Hello?

565
00:35:26,657 --> 00:35:29,659
You found out that the husband
sold Japanese citizenship?

566
00:35:29,660 --> 00:35:33,798
For a million yen,
along with his certificate of residence.

567
00:35:34,999 --> 00:35:37,334
I didn't really expect anything like this.

568
00:35:37,335 --> 00:35:39,036
Who did he sell it to?

569
00:35:39,737 --> 00:35:43,141
To a Filipina named Alisah,
who works at a nightclub called Marmol.

570
00:35:44,909 --> 00:35:46,309
Marmol?

571
00:35:46,310 --> 00:35:47,777
I want to know how much Mrs. Harashima,

572
00:35:47,778 --> 00:35:50,281
who used to work with her, actually knows.

573
00:35:51,015 --> 00:35:52,450
There might be a grudge.

574
00:35:54,352 --> 00:35:56,654
Shakuno, can you look into it?

575
00:35:57,288 --> 00:35:58,122
Yes, sir.

576
00:36:14,739 --> 00:36:15,806
Alisah?

577
00:36:18,743 --> 00:36:22,380
When I first started working there,
she was really nice to me.

578
00:36:24,148 --> 00:36:30,922
But when she found out I was dating Koji,
she became distant all of a sudden.

579
00:36:34,025 --> 00:36:38,796
But in a way, I was relieved because
I didn't want to get too close to her.

580
00:36:40,231 --> 00:36:43,401
What do you mean
you didn't want to get close to her?

581
00:36:44,835 --> 00:36:48,906
I heard she had a shady part-time job
besides working at our club.

582
00:36:50,174 --> 00:36:51,542
A shady part-time job?

583
00:36:56,414 --> 00:36:57,882
I once heard her mention

584
00:36:58,583 --> 00:37:00,751
how "Japanese citizenship"
brings in good money.

585
00:37:01,719 --> 00:37:07,024
And she asked me to let her know if I knew
any Japanese willing to sell theirs.

586
00:37:10,995 --> 00:37:13,396
2.5-MILLION-YEN DEBT

587
00:37:13,397 --> 00:37:17,000
So, this Alisah woman and the husband
were seeing each other?

588
00:37:17,001 --> 00:37:19,703
The husband insists
he wasn't having an affair.

589
00:37:19,704 --> 00:37:22,940
He went to the club after a long time
with his business associates.

590
00:37:23,507 --> 00:37:27,544
That's when he ended up venting
to Alisah about his debt.

591
00:37:27,545 --> 00:37:29,512
She contacted him after a while

592
00:37:29,513 --> 00:37:32,583
and suggested in a cafe
about selling his citizenship.

593
00:37:34,151 --> 00:37:37,188
<i>Koji Harashima has
a pretty serious gambling problem.</i>

594
00:37:38,456 --> 00:37:39,290
Yuki...

595
00:37:40,424 --> 00:37:41,558
What were you thinking?

596
00:37:41,559 --> 00:37:42,892
What on earth were you thinking?

597
00:37:42,893 --> 00:37:43,893
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

598
00:37:43,894 --> 00:37:45,929
What on earth were you thinking?

599
00:37:45,930 --> 00:37:47,031
I'm so sorry.

600
00:37:47,632 --> 00:37:52,036
I will never forgive you
if anything happens to Shun.

601
00:37:53,337 --> 00:37:55,072
<i>He was too desperate for money, I guess.</i>

602
00:37:55,573 --> 00:37:57,474
<i>He didn't even consider</i>

603
00:37:57,475 --> 00:38:00,411
<i>how his citizenship might be used
after selling it.</i>

604
00:38:01,078 --> 00:38:04,815
It would be used as a fake identity
for fraud or something probably.

605
00:38:05,950 --> 00:38:07,184
Whatever it is,

606
00:38:08,085 --> 00:38:11,822
it likely has nothing to do
with this kidnapping incident.

607
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:14,759
- Shakuno.
- Yes?

608
00:38:16,327 --> 00:38:18,863
Can you look into citizenship brokers?

609
00:38:20,197 --> 00:38:22,932
Should we expand the target area
for our investigation?

610
00:38:22,933 --> 00:38:23,967
Certainly.

611
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:25,802
I'll go over the CCTV footage.

612
00:38:25,803 --> 00:38:26,937
Thanks.

613
00:38:28,939 --> 00:38:30,207
That's how I ended up

614
00:38:30,741 --> 00:38:34,312
in charge of investigating
citizenship trafficking.

615
00:38:35,146 --> 00:38:36,380
I see.

616
00:38:37,415 --> 00:38:40,985
I sense that rogue foreigners
are involved in the trafficking.

617
00:38:45,189 --> 00:38:47,557
I wonder if the kidnapping

618
00:38:47,558 --> 00:38:49,527
and the citizenship trade
are completely unrelated.

619
00:38:50,795 --> 00:38:51,961
Excuse me?

620
00:38:51,962 --> 00:38:52,930
Actually...

621
00:38:53,497 --> 00:38:55,833
something about this doesn't feel right.

622
00:38:57,134 --> 00:39:02,072
The kidnapper broke into the living room
while the mother was briefly distracted.

623
00:39:02,073 --> 00:39:05,443
And he managed to take the boy
without being caught on any CCTVs.

624
00:39:07,078 --> 00:39:10,448
It just doesn't seem like the work
of an amateur.

625
00:39:12,249 --> 00:39:14,652
I wonder if some organized group
is involved.

626
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:19,823
I'm sorry, it's not my place.

627
00:39:19,824 --> 00:39:23,561
Now that's what I call
a former cop's instinct!

628
00:39:24,895 --> 00:39:26,030
Well, I mean...

629
00:39:28,499 --> 00:39:29,367
I'm sorry.

630
00:39:30,768 --> 00:39:31,702
Never mind.

631
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:45,249
Please.

632
00:39:46,417 --> 00:39:48,386
Listen to me now.

633
00:39:51,889 --> 00:39:54,691
The police showed up at the club,
snooping around.

634
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:57,061
So what? That has nothing to do with me.

635
00:39:57,762 --> 00:40:00,998
I think it's seriously dangerous
to get more involved with them.

636
00:40:01,999 --> 00:40:05,301
You look suspicious
because you're freaking out.

637
00:40:05,302 --> 00:40:07,405
We're not doing anything wrong.

638
00:40:08,606 --> 00:40:09,439
Alisah.

639
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,941
What is it?

640
00:40:11,642 --> 00:40:14,844
Don't you think
we should go to the police?

641
00:40:14,845 --> 00:40:17,414
For goodness' sake!

642
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:19,817
If you want to go, do it alone.
Don't drag me in.

643
00:40:31,162 --> 00:40:35,666
DAY FOUR SINCE THE KIDNAPPING

644
00:40:58,656 --> 00:41:01,659
Thank you so much. Next in line, please.

645
00:41:02,326 --> 00:41:03,661
Hello, sir.

646
00:41:04,328 --> 00:41:05,696
Is your baby doing well?

647
00:41:06,263 --> 00:41:08,265
Yes, doing very well.

648
00:41:11,802 --> 00:41:13,503
Would you like a <i>"daizi"?</i>

649
00:41:13,504 --> 00:41:14,572
Yes, please.

650
00:41:15,506 --> 00:41:16,807
Okay.

651
00:42:31,148 --> 00:42:32,983
I told you not to smoke there.

652
00:42:33,918 --> 00:42:37,855
Are you worried about my health or what?

653
00:42:39,023 --> 00:42:40,758
I'm not worried about your health.

654
00:42:47,631 --> 00:42:49,500
Seriously,

655
00:42:50,901 --> 00:42:53,704
how much longer do we have to stay here?

656
00:42:54,605 --> 00:42:57,408
Have you heard anything
from our volunteer?

657
00:42:58,275 --> 00:43:01,378
You are awake, huh? It's alright. Come on.

658
00:43:09,787 --> 00:43:14,791
YUKI HARASHIMA, KOJI HARASHIMA

659
00:43:14,792 --> 00:43:15,692
HI. THANK YOU FOR COMING TO
OUR SHOP SO OFTEN.

660
00:43:15,693 --> 00:43:16,593
A FRIEND OF MINE
MADE THIS PORK FLOSS (ROUSONG).

661
00:43:16,594 --> 00:43:17,294
PLEASE LET YOUR CHILD HAVE A TASTE TOO.

662
00:43:19,530 --> 00:43:22,132
You've got a great appetite again today.

663
00:43:22,766 --> 00:43:24,801
- Is it good?
- Is it good?

664
00:43:24,802 --> 00:43:26,604
There. I'm done.

665
00:43:27,838 --> 00:43:29,173
Tell me what you think.

666
00:43:34,044 --> 00:43:35,745
- This is great.
- Perfect.

667
00:43:35,746 --> 00:43:37,113
Yes!

668
00:43:37,114 --> 00:43:39,649
- It's good.
- Thank you. I'm so glad.

669
00:43:39,650 --> 00:43:41,784
You did such a great job.

670
00:43:41,785 --> 00:43:43,954
It's finally ready.

671
00:43:44,588 --> 00:43:47,090
I packed a lot of <i>rousong</i> in here.

672
00:43:47,091 --> 00:43:49,326
Thanks a lot, Auntie Ma.

673
00:43:52,363 --> 00:43:55,331
It's happening.
The diaper shoplifter is here.

674
00:43:55,332 --> 00:43:57,635
<i>I'm making an exception this time.
You come along.</i>

675
00:43:58,769 --> 00:44:01,237
Could it be this child?

676
00:44:01,238 --> 00:44:04,273
<i>I haven't quite figured it out yet.</i>

677
00:44:04,274 --> 00:44:05,676
<i>I can't tell if you're a good person</i>

678
00:44:06,310 --> 00:44:07,444
or a bad person.

679
00:44:08,178 --> 00:44:09,947
You are such a good kid.

680
00:44:12,383 --> 00:44:14,451
- You're such a good girl.
- She is.

681
00:44:18,722 --> 00:44:19,823
Do you want to come here?

682
00:44:20,691 --> 00:44:22,926
Do you want Grandma?
